Masters (MS) in Computer Science in Canada - Best universities, Requirements, Scholarships and Jobs

  • 233 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Jun 08,2023 03:53 PM IST

Pursuing a Masters in Computer science in Canada is a good option for students. The country has a strong reputation for its world-class education system and multicultural environment. Read the blog to explore why Canada is an ideal destination for a masters in computer science, the top universities’ scholarships and funding opportunities, and job prospects after graduation.

Canada has established a global leader in computer science, with its universities consistently ranking among the top in the world. Its commitment to innovation and research is evident in thriving tech hubs. Pursuing a masters in computer science in Canada is an attractive choice for students who wish to be at the forefront of technological advancements and directly impact the industry’s future.

In addition to academic excellence and research opportunities, Canada offers a good quality of life, affordable tuition fee, and a welcoming environment for international students. This blog will provide information about the best universities for MS in Computer Science with eligibility, requirement and scholarships.

Advantages of pursuing MS in Computer Science in Canada:

Pursuing a masters in computer science in Canada has numerous benefits that can significantly impact personal and professional growth.

•High-quality Education:
Many institutions are ranked among the best in the world and provide research facilities, experienced faculty. Canada is known for its best quality education.

•Affordable Tuition fees:
Compared to other study destinations such as the USA or the UK, tuition fee in Canada are generally lower, making it a more accessible option for international students. The universities/colleges also provide scholarships and bursaries.

•Work Opportunities:
Canada provides international students with various post-graduation work permits and employment opportunities. These possibilities can aid students in developing their professional skills.

•Multicultural environment:
It is known for its cultural diversity and welcoming towards international students. Studying in Canada will expose the different cultures and viewpoints, which can benefit personal and professional growth.

Admission Requirements for MS in Computer Science:

Admission requirements for an MS in computer science in Canada generally include the following:

  • Applicant must have a bachelor's degree or equivalent, with required and pre-requisite subjects/courses.
  • Applicant must have a required minimum score in an English language test such as TOEFL, IELTS or PTE. The score varies by university and program.
  • A GRE score may be required for some universities, although this is optional.
  • Some other documents required for admission:
     1.Letters of recommendation (LOR) - applicant’s academic achievements and relevant professional experience.
    2. Statement of purpose (SOP): highlighting the applicant’s career goals, research interests, and reasons for pursuing a masters in computer science in   Canada.
    3.A resume or CV detailing the applicant's academic background, work experience, research projects, and any relevant skills or achievements.

It's essential to do proper research about the specific admission requirements for each program as it differs from university to university.

Job prospects after completing MS in Computer Science in Canada:

Job opportunities for computer science graduates in Canada are excellent, with a high demand for experienced professionals in various fields. The following are some of the initiatives for computer science graduates:

  • Software development /engineering
  • Data science and analytics
  • Artificial intelligence and machine learning
  • Cybersecurity
  • Game design and development
  • Human-computer interaction and user experience design

Graduates can find employment with multinational companies, start-ups, research institutions, and government organizations. Moreover, the Canadian government has implemented policies to retain international students after graduation, such as the Post-Graduation Work Permit Program (PGWP), which allows graduates to work in Canada for up to three years.

Tips for Successful Application:

Here are guidelines to help:

  • Start researching universities and programs
  • Applicant must search for admission requirements for the program as different universities have different requirements.
  • Make sure the applicant should highlight academic achievements and extracurricular activities in the personal statement (SOP).
  • International students must meet English Proficiency Language test scores, such as IELTS, TOEFL and PTE.
  • Check all the deadlines before applying to the university.
  • Keep track of all the documents and deadlines.

CONCLUSION:

Pursuing study in Canada for MS in Computer Science is an excellent opportunity for international students. Choosing one of the best universities, students can help develop a strong computer science foundation to build a professional career. For more information, visit the nearest Canam Office and interact with study abroad professionals about choosing the best university for MS in Computer Science in Canada.

FAQ

Does Canada require the GRE for MS in Computer Science?
Most universities accept only IELTS, TOEFL, PTE or DUOLONGO scores for admission.  GRE score is not compulsory.
What are the opportunities for MS in Computer Science in Canada?
MS in computer science opens up various opportunities such as Software developers, Project Managers, Network engineers, IT consultants and more.

What is the duration for MS in Computer Science?
The duration for an MS in Computer Science is generally one-two years.
What is the minimum CGPA required for MS in Computer Science in Canada?
Most universities/colleges require a minimum CGPA of 65%   to qualify for the desired program. Along with CGPA, English Language Test scores such as IELTS or TOEFL are also needed.
Which universities in Canada are suitable for MS in Computer Science?
The University of Waterloo and the University of Ottawa are some of the universities in Canada for MS in Computer Science programs.
